The paper deals with the design of space codes for optical wireless communication systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The use of Farey sequences in number theory to solve the design problem suggests a possible connection to optimization and algorithms (cs.OH). The discussion of diversity gain and error performance is related to signal processing (cs.SI) and network theory (cs.NT).
